metadata.name: Galdricge #157
metadata.description:
Galdricge, meaning 'Enchantress' in Anglo-Saxon, is an attempt to evoke a sense of grace and femininity from stark, abstract elements. 


Add "&png" to querystring for 2048x2048 png export 
Add "&svg" for svg export. There are up to 5 layers which can be controlled in Inkscape for different pen widths and colours 


This work is plottable thanks to open-sourced code and article from twilliability. Check out his plotter pieces at https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/twilliability  
Article : https://jealousmarkup.xyz/texts/webgl-line-hiding 
Code : https://gist.github.com/gugray/dfdbef073a3efe1abb5f501728ac9d51 


Other libs (refer console output for license info) 
Graphics : PIXIJS https://github.com/pixijs/pixijs 
Geometry : JSTS https://github.com/bjornharrtell/jsts 
Noise : SIMPLEX-NOISE https://github.com/jwagner/simplex-noise.js 
Random number lib : Fdrandom.js https://github.com/strainer/fdrandom.js 


Made on and off, over 5 months of the great 2023 bear market.

metadata.name: the endless dance #50
metadata.description:
“We thought of life by analogy with a journey, a pilgrimage, which had a serious purpose at the end, and the thing was to get to that end, success or whatever it is, maybe heaven after you’re dead. But we missed the point the whole way along. It was a musical thing and you were supposed to sing or to dance while the music was being played.” ― Alan Watts

Controls
spacebar: pause/unpause
mousedown: overdraw
x key: clear canvas

enjoy the dance

metadata.name: GuageTiles #10
metadata.description:
An interactive tiled pattern is generated with the fxhash which determines two features at random.

"groundsState" value determines a base configuration and is sampled uniformly at random in the range 0 to 1.

"spectralGap" determines the color of the pattern and comes in three types::
'low' (30%) is monochrome
'mid' (60%) is small hue range
'high' (10%) is a large hue range

*click/touch & hold/move* the canvas to charge the pattern and change the flux mode of the tiles.
*release* the canvas and the pattern decays back to its "groundState" value.

metadata.name: ThetaStar #33
metadata.description:
A "ThetaStar" is generated through an Iterated Function System determined by the fxhash with one main feature 'Theta' corresponding to an angle value in radians sampled uniformly at random in the range 2.5 < Theta < 3.0.

**Click / Touch** the canvas to reset and watch the "ThetaStar" gradually radiate in full spectrum.
The visually daring may **Rapidly Click / Touch** for an enhanced strobe like effect.

NOTE TO COLLECTORS:

This token will be sold as a Dutch auction. Every 5 minutes, the price will change based on the following schedule:
20 / 15 / 10 / 5 / 2 tez

After that, the price will remain fixed at 2 tez.
If there are tokens remaining after 72 hours, they will be burnt.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

0xFoif

Inspired by Tyler Hobbs' water color studies and the splitting algorithm of 0xDrue, 0xFoif is a collection of interplay between a strong grid with clear cut splits and a blurriness introduced by multiple transparent layers.

Zürich/Quito, January 2022
❤️ pifragile
